{
  "stem": "19550.5",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We dreamed and-- and attempted, somehow, to make contact with my father and thought maybe he can save us in the last moment.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, we-- we couldn't.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had, for several years, maintained contact with my father through Switzerland, but you couldn't even post a letter.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, if you had posted a letter, by the time it arrived in Switzerland we were burned.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, you know, discussing is there a way in which we can notify our father and maybe he can do something, some-- invoke some kind of a deus ex machina and save us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] We were, of course, all trying to somehow fortify and-- and save each other, in all sorts of ways that we could.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had actually left the ghetto once, having being firmly convinced that it was a hopeless situation, and believing that, you know, whoever can should save himself so there will be a [INAUDIBLE] Israel, a remnant.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But, as so many others, I couldn't countenance leaving my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I came back voluntarily and have been, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] and it's a peculiar word to use for something like that, but I have been happy ever since that I have done it, that I have been able to provide some comfort, some easement, some encouragement, some strength for the rest of my family.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the same goes for them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They, I'm sure, felt the same way.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Sorry?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At one time, you know, we bought off the gendarme, who was our guard.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
